Competition No.: CUPE C-22-0270UE
POSTED: October 5, 2022
DEADLINE: 4:30 p.m October 21, 2022


Admissions Assistant
1 – Permanent Position
International Students and Admissions Office
CUPE Local 4400, Unit C – Grade J (12 Month)
$27.40 – $32.64 per hour





The Toronto District School Board adheres to equitable hiring, employment and promotion practices.
Reporting to the Manager, International Students and Admissions Office, the Admissions Assistant will be
responsible for handling all aspects of the application process of international students and to handle
routine inquiries about admission of non-resident pupils in TDSB schools. Also, to provide administrative
and secretarial support to the Manager, International Students & Admissions Office. This includes word
processing and database management, arranging meetings, preparing reports, and preparing routine
correspondence, working with SAP and SIS, responding to general queries and analyzing information for
the Manager. The work will also involve maintaining the orderly flow of information and accurate record
keeping for the office including enrollment of international students, health insurance information,
information from Planning Department, admission letters etc.

Summary of Duties:
➢ Provide information to clients (walk-in and overseas inquiries) on the international student program, and
routine admissions questions, for students who may have to pay fees;
➢ Receive and process all international student applications;
➢ Contact schools regarding placement of international students;
➢ Prepare all correspondence/forms related to international students and other admission categories;
➢ Administer the appropriate documentation to indemnify the Board from any liability;
➢ Work with the TDSB approved agents to register students;
➢ Manage the appropriate paperwork and documentation in relation to payment of agents;
➢ Work with the approved Health Insurance carriers and maintain associated records;
➢ Maintain office records;
➢ Review mail and prepare responses;
➢ Maintain confidential files for Manager;
➢ Research and collect information for reports;
➢ Prepare presentations using various software applications;
➢ Assist with the monitoring of department budget;
➢ Schedule appointments and meetings;
➢ Assist other staff and provide back-up as required;
➢ Liaise with schools, administrative departments, and external organizations;
➢ Act as resource person for general inquiries from the public and staff, regarding international students
and admission requirements for non-resident students;
➢ Communicate regularly with Board staff and the general public; and
➢ Other related duties as assigned.


Qualifications:
➢ Secondary School Diploma including computer courses with three years related administrative
experience, or an equivalent combination of education and experience;
➢ Proficient keyboarding skills and expertise in the use of computer technology, including word processing,
Admissions Assistant
spreadsheets, databases, e-mail, presentation packages, Student Information Systems, HR/Payroll and
Financial applications;
➢ Ability to communicate in a sensitive, courteous manner with students, parents, community members,
staff, and the general public with a customer service focus;
➢ Working knowledge of related legislation: Board policies and procedures, and Ministry policies;
➢ Understanding of related government documents and forms;
➢ Proven ability to work under pressure in order to meet frequent deadlines;
➢ Ability to take initiative, work independently, and maintain confidential information in a circumspect
manner; and
➢ Good organizational skills.

Assets:
➢ Fluency in speaking a second language.

Location: 5050 Yonge Street (wheelchair accessible)


Hours: 35 hours per week


Work Year: 12 months


Notes:
1. It is anticipated that interviews will take place within two weeks after the closing date of this
competition.
2. It is anticipated that the successful applicant will commence as soon as possible and practical.

Please note:
Applications must be submitted:
1. In résumé form with a covering letter to: Application.Submission@tdsb.on.ca
2. With competition # CUPE C-22-0270UE in the subject line
3. Apply no later than 4:30pm on October 21, 2022

Only applicants selected for an interview will be contacted. Applications will not be acknowledged in writing.

We strive to meet the accommodation needs of persons with disabilities. Applicants are encouraged to
make their needs for accommodation known in advance, during the hiring process.
