Ontario Health actively seeks candidates who are First Nations, Métis, Inuit, and urban Indigenous; Francophone; Black and racialized; members of 2SLGBTQIA+ communities; trans and nonbinary; and disabled.
Want to make a difference in your career? Consider this opportunity.
Reporting to the Group Manager, Program Management (Cancer Screening Operations), the Analyst, Operational Reporting will be responsible for supporting the data analysis and production of reports/dashboards to inform the day-to-day operations of the Cancer Screening Programs and informed decision-making for the management team.
The Analyst, Operational Reporting will provide a tactical and detailed view of the Cancer Screening Operations (i.e., data analysis, visualization and interpretation) with key daily aspects/outputs and immediate necessities, highlighting key areas of need or concern that are immediately actionable. Additionally, the Analyst, Operational Reporting will deliver business insights and trends for business decision-making (e.g., opportunities for operational efficiencies).
The Product Management Cancer Services (PMCS) team administers the assets used for data collection and storage and provides access to the data required by the Analyst, Operational Reporting (e.g., system queries and/or extracts) for the analysis, automation and visualization in MS Access, SAS, Excel, Power BI and other tools.
Here is what you will be doing:
Develop, manage and maintain MS Access databases, including database design, user access controls, user interfaces, queries, macros, integration with external data sources, database administration, backup and restore;
Maintain all data with Personal Health Information (PHI) in a secure manner per provincial and OH’s legislation, policies, procedures and best practices/standards;
Ensure robust risk management environment with respect to the protection of PHI, and develop and implement risk and issues identification and mitigation strategies;
Design, develop, and maintain key performance indicators (KPIs), operational reports and dashboards, representing data visually and identifying data anomalies, trends and outliers, and recommend targets;
Gather and document business requirements in support of developing reporting solutions to address business needs and translate information into technical requirements for development;
Plan and facilitate meetings and working sessions for requirements gathering, validation and acceptance of reports;
Identify, communicate and recommend improvements for data or process flaws or limitations in data sources or analysis;
Prepare, deliver, and present reports/results/findings from a technical and business perspective;
Apply basic project management methodologies to daily work, including scoping, planning, scheduling, change control, risk/issue management and document accordingly.
Prepare and maintain technical documentation and standard operating procedures for databases and reports, including data sources, methodologies, activities, frequency, audience, etc.;
Keep abreast of Cancer Screening’s data sources (e.g., databases and systems), updates and upgrades, representing the needs of Operations when updates or new developments take place.
Identify improvement opportunities and enhance existing Program Management’s databases, reports and processes;
Evaluate and recommend to the Program Management team new technologies, tools and leading practices when applicable;
Proactively share knowledge across project teams, as appropriate;
Perform cross-functional and/or other duties consistent with the job classification, as assigned or requested.
Here is what you will need to be successful:
Education:
Post-secondary degree or diploma in a computer-related field or equivalent work experience, required;
Knowledge/Experience:
Minimum 4 years of related working experience;
Proficiency in MS Access and Excel, required;
Read and write VBA, SQL and SAS, required;
Proficiency in SAS Viya and/or Power BI, an asset.
Skills/Abilities:
Advanced computer skills and knowledge of the entire MS Office suite;
Intermediate to advanced proficiency in analytical and reporting tools;
Demonstrated proficiency in database design, information management, database integration, data security, and system optimization;
Ability to extract data from various relational databases and other technology systems;
Experience creating and manipulating interactive digital dashboards from multiple data sources;
Excellent knowledge of electronic information systems, information privacy and security;
Excellent interpersonal and communications (verbal, written, presentation) skills;
Demonstrated ability to manage multiple tasks simultaneously, adjusting to issues as needed in a dynamic work environment.
Superior ability to analyze and define problems, evaluate alternatives, find solutions and make recommendations;
Detail-oriented with strong critical thinking;
Strong analytical skills with creative/innovative thinking.
Physical Demands
Work involves minimal physical effort normally associated with a corporate office environment.
Most work is completed at a desk or conference table
Long periods of sitting and regular computer/phone use
Has freedom to move about or change position at will
Visual Demands (level and intensity)
Reads a variety of data tables, including charts
Ability to read a computer screen for e-mail, preparing documents and reports
Auditory Demands
Position functions in a typical office environment or a work from home environment (can achieve work remotely)
Concentration Demands (level and intensity)
There is frequent need to give concentrated attention, with one or two senses at a time.
Absorbs information from multiple participants in teleconference meetings
Absorbs, analyzes and translates complex data into reports
Must be able to listen to different viewpoints, clarify messages and use information to create solutions
Responds to multiple priorities and quick turnaround demands
There is continuous pressure from deadlines, for accuracy, or similar demands
There is flexibility to change work activities, take a break or alter work position
Employment Type: Permanent Full Time
Paygrade and Zone: 4A
Location: Ontario (currently virtual; subject to change)
All applicants must be a resident of Ontario to be considered for roles at Ontario Health.
Internal Application Deadline Date: September 19 2022
We encourage applicants with accessibility needs to notify us if they have any accommodation needs in the application and/or interview process.

We are looking for experienced developers to join our Global Customer Support team with 100 committed consultants and developers. We deliver high-quality support to over 200 clients worldwide for their SimCorp Dimension investment management platform.
The Global Support team provides business and code solutions to problems within SimCorp products. As a Senior Developer, you will be responsible to find solid solutions for varying challenges in collaboration with the team. As such you play an important role as a link between our clients in the market and software engineers in SimCorp's Product Development.
Your responsibilities
Work with support consultants and other developers to analyze and solve issues that occur in SimCorp Dimension at our clients;
Co-operate with clients to understand their use of the system and translate this into code solutions;
Debug code and create a business or technical solutions;
Create code specifications for the solutions;
Create code to execute it on the client side to make their database updated;
Be an important interface to SimCorp’s Product Development;
Act as lead or mentor for existing team members;
Work on explaining the technicalities to the non-technical world;
Willingness to work on weekends (approx. once per month) and occasionally extended hours to support our clients;
Business travels to our clients or other SimCorp offices may be required from time to time;
Your qualifications
Significant experience in a similar position;
Relevant college diploma or university degree;
Programming experience, in C# and readiness, to learn other programming languages such as APL
https://tryapl.org/
;
Prior financial knowledge desired;
Fluency in English.
About us
SimCorp is a provider of investment management solutions to the world's largest asset managers, fund managers, asset servicers, pension and insurance funds, wealth managers, banks and sovereign wealth funds.
Here you will work with experienced and supportive colleagues. We are more than 1900 employees from 50+ nationalities dedicated to supporting our 200+ clients across the globe.
We celebrate multiple approaches and points of view, together we're building a culture where difference is valued. You will be part of a success story and a company that continues to grow, offering a lot of interesting opportunities.
Visit our career pages to learn why other people choose to work at SimCorp:
www.simcorp.com/career
Are you interested?
Kindly send in your application in English.
For further information please contact Kristina Manukyan, Talent Acquisition Partner (
kristina.manukyan@simcorp.com
).
We are looking forward to talking with you!
